The paper deals with entity alignment in knowledge graphs, which is a task related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves graph convolutional networks (GCNs) and attentive interactions, which are common techniques in the field of graph-based machine learning and can be categorized under cs.DB (databases) and cs.CL (computational linguistics). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on cross-lingual datasets, which is a task related to information retrieval (cs.IR).
